# White background for combined plots

  grobTree(
    rectGrob(
      gp = gpar(
        fill = 'white', 
        lwd = 0)), 
    gg)  
}

# Extract a legend from the plot
# From here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13649473/add-a-common-legend-for-combined-ggplots
g_legend <- function(a.gplot){
  tmp <- ggplot_gtable(ggplot_build(a.gplot))
  leg <- which(sapply(tmp$grobs, function(x) x$name) == "guide-box")
  legend <- tmp$grobs[[leg]]
  return(legend)
}
## Functions that make tables

## Descriptive statistics
Descr <- function(x) {
    x <- na.omit(x)
    n <- length(x)
    M <- mean(x)
    SD <- sd(x)
    
    data.frame(
      M = M,
      M_95CI = 
        sprintf(
          '%0.3f; %0.3f',
          M + qnorm(0.025) * SD / sqrt(n),
          M + qnorm(0.975) * SD / sqrt(n)
        ),
      SD = SD,
      median = median(x),
      min = min(x),
      max = max(x)
    )  
}


## Descriptive statistics
descr_table <- function(
  d, vars, gr, 
  ff = list(
    M = mean, 
    SD = sd
  ),
  ...
) {
  require(mlth.data.frame)

  appff <- function(ff, x, ...) {
    as.data.frame(
      lapply(ff, function(f) f(x, ...))
    )
  }
  
  d <- d[, c(gr, vars)]
  d <- d[rowSums(is.na(d)) < ncol(d), ]
  d[, gr] <- factor(d[, gr])
  
  outp <- mlth.data.frame(
    gr = levels(d[, gr])
  )
  names(outp)[1] <- gr
  
  for (i in vars) {
    outp[[i]] <- do.call(
      'rbind',
      by(
        d[, i],
        d[, gr],
        appff,
        ff = ff,
        ...
      )
    )
  }
  
  return(outp)
}

## Ridge plot
ridges <- function(gg) {
  gg + 
    geom_density_ridges(
      panel_scaling = FALSE,
      scale = 0.9,
      alpha = 0.4,
      quantile_lines = TRUE,
      quantiles = c(0.25, 0.5, 0.75),
      vline_color = '#00000066',
      jittered_points = TRUE,
      position = position_points_jitter(
        width = 0.05,
        height = 0
      ),
      point_shape = '|',
      point_size = 2,
      point_alpha = 1
    ) +
    ylab('Grade') +
    theme_classic() +
    theme(
      axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
      axis.text.y = element_text(
        size = 12
      ),
      axis.title.x = element_text(

      )
    )
}

## Correlation plot
cor_plot <- function(gg) {
  rho <- cor.test(
    layer_data(gg)$x,
    layer_data(gg)$y,
    method = 'spearman'
  )
  
  cor_label <- 
    bquote(
      rho == .(three_digits(rho$estimate)) *
      .(case_when(
        rho$p.value <= 0.001 ~ '***',
        rho$p.value <= 0.01 ~ '**',
        rho$p.value <= 0.05 ~ '*',
        TRUE ~ ''
      ))
    )
  
  gg +
    geom_point(
      size = 3,
      alpha = 0.5
    ) +
    scale_color_brewer(
      palette = 'Dark2'
    ) +
    annotation_custom(
      textGrob(
        cor_label,
        x = unit(0.95, 'npc'),
        y = unit(0.95, 'npc'),
        hjust = 1,
        vjust = 1,
        gp = gpar(
          fontsize = 16
        )
      )
    ) +
    theme_classic() +
    theme(
      legend.title = element_blank(),
      legend.position = 'top',
      axis.title = element_text(
        size = 12
      ),
      axis.title.y = element_text(
        angle = 0,
        vjust = 0.5
      )
    )
}

Statistical analysis

This section performs statistical analysis and extracts the indices and statistical parameters that will be presented in Results.

## Applying the models of numeric representation

R2 <- function(m, r) {
  1 - sum(residuals(m)^2) / 
    sum((r - mean(r, na.rm = TRUE))^2, na.rm = TRUE)
}

model_sum <- NULL

for (i in unique(data_long$login)) {
  grade <- data_long %>%
    filter(login == i) %>%
    pull(class) %>%
    unique
  
  D0 <- data_long %>%
    filter(login == i) 
  D <- D0 %>%
    filter(rt > 1)
  
  fits_i <- NULL
  r2 <- NA
  
  if (nrow(D) >= 15) {
    # Fit the models
    # Flat
    M0 <- D %>%
      lm(resp ~ 1, data = .)
    
    # Flat (non-linear)
    ones <- rep(1, nrow(D))
    M0_2 <- D %>%
      nlsLM(
        resp ~ a * ones,
        start = list(a = 500),
        data = .
      )
    
    # Linear
    M1 <- D %>%
      lm(resp ~ stim, data = .)
    
    # Logarithmic
    M2 <- D %>%
      lm(resp ~ log(stim), data = .)
    
    # Proportional
    M3 <- D %>%
      nlsLM(
        resp ~ W * (stim^beta) / (stim^beta + (W - stim)^beta), 
        data = .,
        start = list(beta = 1.1, W = 1100),
        control = list(maxiter = 200)
      )
    
    fits_i <- rbind(
      Flat = c(AIC = AIC(M0), BIC = BIC(M0), R2 = NA),
      Linear = c(AIC = AIC(M1), BIC = BIC(M1), R2 = R2(M1, D$resp)),
      Logarithmic = c(AIC = AIC(M2), BIC = BIC(M2), R2 = R2(M2, D$resp)),
      Proportional = c(AIC = AIC(M3), BIC = BIC(M3), R2 = R2(M3, D$resp))
    )
    
    # Decide which model is better
    aov1 <- anova(M0, M1)
    aov2 <- anova(M0, M2)
    aov3 <- anova(M0_2, M3)
    
    if (
      aov1[2, 'Pr(>F)'] > 0.05 &&
      aov2[2, 'Pr(>F)'] > 0.05 &&
      aov3[2, 'Pr(>F)'] > 0.05
    ) {
      best_model <- 'random response'
    } else {
      min_aic <- which.min(fits_i[, 'AIC'])
      min_bic <- which.min(fits_i[, 'BIC'])
      max_r2 <- which.max(fits_i[, 'R2'])
      
      if (
        all.equal(min_aic, min_bic, max_r2)
      ) {
        best_model <- switch(
          min_aic,
          NA,
          'linear',
          'logarithmic',
          'proportional'
        )
        r2 <- max(fits_i[, 'R2'], na.rm = TRUE)
      } else {
        best_model <- 'N/A (conflicting criteria)'
      }
    }
  } else {
    best_model <- 'N/A (lack of data)'
  }
  
  model_sum[[as.character(i)]] <- list(
    id = as.character(i),
    grade = grade,
    valid_trials = nrow(D),
    best_model = best_model,
    r2 = r2,
    fit_table = fits_i,
    medRT = median(D$rt, na.rm = TRUE),
    acc = mean(D$acc, na.rm = TRUE),
    models = list(
      flat = M0,
      linear = M1,
      log = M2,
      prop = M3
    ),
    data = D0
  )
}

model_summary <- model_sum %>%
  lapply(
    function(x) {
      data.frame(
        id = x$id,
        grade = x$grade,
        best_model = x$best_model,
        n = x$valid_trials,
        r2 = x$r2,
        medRT = x$medRT,
        acc = x$acc
      )
    }
  ) %>%
  do.call('rbind', .)

grobs <- list()

# This function returns the function of the best fitting model
choose_model <- function(best_model, Ms) {
  M <- switch(
    best_model,
    logarithmic = Ms$log,
    linear = Ms$linear,
    proportional = Ms$prop,
    NULL
  )
  
  switch(
    best_model,
    'linear' = function(x) { M$coefficients[1] + x * M$coefficients[2] },
    'logarithmic' = function(x) { M$coefficients[1] + log(x) * M$coefficients[2] },
    'proportional' = function(x) {
      beta <- M %>% summary %>% `$`('coefficients') %>% `[`('beta', 'Estimate')
      W <- M %>% summary %>% `$`('coefficients') %>% `[`('W', 'Estimate')
      W * (x^beta) / (x^beta + (W - x)^beta)
    },
    NULL)
}

for (i in c('logarithmic', 'linear', 'proportional')) {

## The plots with individual responses and selected model for each student
##     incl. Figures 2-4

for (i in model_summary$id) {
  grade <- model_summary %>%
    filter(id == i) %>%
    pull(grade)

  best_model <- model_summary %>%
    filter(id == i) %>%
    pull(best_model) %>%
    as.character()
  
  M <- switch(
    best_model,
    'random response' = model_sum[[i]]$models$flat,
    'linear' = model_sum[[i]]$models$linear,
    'logarithmic' = model_sum[[i]]$models$log,
    'proportional' = model_sum[[i]]$models$prop,
    'N/A (lack of data)' = NULL
  )
  

  Cols <- wes_palette('Darjeeling1', 4, type = 'continuous')
  Cols <- Cols[c(1, 1, 3, 2, 4, 4)]
  ColsBnW <- sequential_hcl(4, 'Grays')
  ColsBnW <- ColsBnW[c(1, 1, 2, 3, 4, 4)]
    
  ## Pull the data
  D <- data_long %>%
    filter(login == i) %>%
    mutate(
      rt_group = cut(
        rt,
        c(0, 1, 2.5, 5, 7.5, 10, max(rt))),
      label = case_when(
        as.integer(rt_group) %in% c(1, 6)  ~ sprintf('%0.1fs', rt),
        TRUE ~ NA_character_
      )
    )
  
  Dfit <- D %>%
    filter(rt > 1) %>%
    filter(!is.na(resp)) %>%
    pull(resp)

  Mcoef <- coef(M)

  best_model_message <- glue('Best model: {best_model}')
  if (best_model %in% c('linear', 'logarithmic', 'proportional'))
    best_model_message <- bquote(
      .(best_model_message) * ',' ~ R^2 == .(three_digits(R2(M, Dfit)))
      * ',' ~ .(switch(
        best_model,
        'linear' = glue(
          'k0 = {three_digits(Mcoef["(Intercept)"])}, ',
          'k1 = {three_digits(Mcoef["stim"])}'
        ),
        'logarithmic' = glue(
          'k0 = {three_digits(Mcoef["(Intercept)"])}, ',
          'k1 = {three_digits(Mcoef["log(stim)"])}'
        ),
        'proportional' = glue(
          '\U03B2 = {three_digits(Mcoef["beta"])}, ', 
          'W = {floor(Mcoef["W"])}'
        )
      ))
    )
  
  
  best_model_fun <- switch(
    best_model,
    'random response' = function(x) { Mcoef[1] },
    'linear' = function(x) { Mcoef[1] + x * Mcoef[2] },
    'logarithmic' = function(x) { Mcoef[1] + log(x) * Mcoef[2] },
    'proportional' = function(x) {
      Mcoef['W'] * (x^Mcoef['beta']) / (x^Mcoef['beta'] + (Mcoef['W'] - x)^Mcoef['beta'])
    },
    NULL)

  ## Compose the plot
  gg <- D %>% ggplot(
    aes(
      x = stim, y = resp,
      fill = rt_group,
      shape = rt_group,
      label = label
    )
  ) +
    geom_abline(
      slope = 1, 
      intercept = 0, 
      color = 'grey36', 
      linetype = 'dotted'
    ) +
    stat_function(
      fun = best_model_fun
    ) +
    geom_point(
      color = 'grey36',
      alpha = 0.8,
      size = 3
    ) +
    geom_text_repel(
      nudge_y = 30
    ) +
    scale_fill_manual(
      drop = FALSE,
      na.translate = FALSE,
      values = Cols,
      name = 'Response time',
      labels = c(
        '< 1.0s', '1.0-2.5s', 
        '2.5-5.0s', '5.0-7.5s', 
        '7.5-10s', '> 10s'
      )
    ) +
    scale_shape_manual(
      values = c(24, 21, 21, 21, 21, 25),
      drop = FALSE,
      na.translate = FALSE,
      name = 'Response time',
      labels = c(
        '< 1.0s', '1.0-2.5s', 
        '2.5-5.0s', '5.0-7.5s', 
        '7.5-10s', '> 10s'
      )
    ) +
    ggtitle(
      label = glue('id = { i }, Grade { grade }'),
      subtitle = best_model_message
    ) +
    xlab('Stimulus') + 
    ylab('Response') +
    xlim(0, 1000) + 
    ylim(0, 1000) +
    theme_classic()
  
  ggsave(
    glue('figures/resp_plots/{ 
            switch(
              best_model, 
              "random response" = "rand",
              "N/A (lack of data)" = "na",
              "logarithmic" = "log", 
              "linear" = "lin", 
              "proportional" = "prop"
            ) 
          }-{ sprintf("%02.0f", grade) }-{ i }.png'
    ),
    plot = gg,
    device = 'png',
    height = 7,
    width = 7,
    units = 'in'
  )
  
  ggsave(
    glue('figures/resp_plots_bnw/{ 
            switch(
              best_model, 
              "random response" = "rand",
              "N/A (lack of data)" = "na",
              "logarithmic" = "log", 
              "linear" = "lin", 
              "proportional" = "prop"
            ) 
          }-{ sprintf("%02.0f", grade) }-{ i }-bnw.png'
    ),
    plot = 
      gg +
      scale_fill_manual(
        drop = FALSE,
        na.translate = FALSE,
        values = ColsBnW,
        name = 'Response time',
        labels = c(
          '< 1.0s', '1.0-2.5s', 
          '2.5-5.0s', '5.0-7.5s', 
          '7.5-10s', '> 10s'
        )
      ),
    device = 'png',
    height = 7,
    width = 7,
    units = 'in'
  )
}

## Table 4. The proportion of pupils with proportional representation with different value of a parameter “beta”(exponent)

prop_data %>%
  filter(best_model == 'proportional') %>%
  mutate(
    beta_pos = case_when(
      beta >= 1 ~ '>= 1',
      TRUE ~ '< 1'
    ),
    beta_pos = factor(
      beta_pos,
      levels = c('< 1', '>= 1')
    )
  ) %>%
  with(
    table(grade, beta_pos)
  ) %>%
  apply(1, function(x) {
    sprintf(
      '%0.0f%%',
      100 * x / sum(x))
  }) %>%
  t %>%
  `colnames<-`(
    c('beta < 1', 'beta >= 1')
  ) %>%
  as.data.frame %>%
  kable2(
    row.names = TRUE,
    align = 'c',
    caption = 'Table 4. The proportion of pupils with proportional representation with different value of a parameter “beta”(exponent)'
  ) %>%
  kable_styling

## Figure 5. The distribution of R2 for linear and proportional models

gg <- model_sum_table %>%
  filter(
    best_model %in% c(
      'linear', 'proportional'
    )
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    grade = factor(
      grade, 
      levels = 1:11
    ),
    best_model = factor(
      best_model,
      levels = c(
        'proportional', 'linear'
      )
    ),
    medAcc = {
      MA <- rep_len(NA, length(acc))
           for (i in unique(grade)) {
             MA[which(grade == i)][1] <- 
               median(acc[grade == i], na.rm = TRUE)
           }
           MA
         },
         medAcc = case_when(
           is.na(medAcc) ~ NA_character_,

## Figure 6. The distribution of parameters of linear model 
##           from grade 4 to grade 11

lin_k0 <- lin_data %>%
  filter(grade >= 4) %>%
  mutate(
    grade = factor(grade, levels = 11:4)
  ) %>%
  filter(table(grade)[grade] > 1) %>%
  filter(
    k0 >= quantile(k0, 0.25) - 1.5 * IQR(k0) &
      k0 <= quantile(k0, 0.75) + 1.5 * IQR(k0)
  ) %>%
  ggplot(
    aes(x = k0, y = grade)
  ) %>%
  ridges

lin_k1 <- lin_data %>%
  filter(grade >= 4) %>%
  mutate(
    grade = factor(grade, levels = 11:4)
  ) %>%
  filter(table(grade)[grade] > 1) %>%
  filter(
    k1 >= quantile(k1, 0.25) - 1.5 * IQR(k1) &
      k1 <= quantile(k1, 0.75) + 1.5 * IQR(k1)
  ) %>%
  ggplot(
    aes(x = k1, y = grade)
  ) %>%
  ridges +
  scale_y_discrete(
    position = 'right'
  )

gg <- arrangeGrob(
  lin_k0, lin_k1,
    ncol = 2,
    clip = FALSE
  ) %>%
  white_bg

## Figure 7. Association between intercept and slope in linear model

gg <- lin_data %>%
  filter(grade >= 4) %>%
  mutate(
    grade = factor(grade, levels = 11:4)
  ) %>%
  filter(table(grade)[grade] > 1) %>%
  filter(
    k0 >= quantile(k0, 0.25) - 1.5 * IQR(k0) &
      k0 <= quantile(k0, 0.75) + 1.5 * IQR(k0)
  ) %>%
  filter(
    k1 >= quantile(k1, 0.25) - 1.5 * IQR(k1) &
      k1 <= quantile(k1, 0.75) + 1.5 * IQR(k1)
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    grade2 = case_when(
      grade %in% 1:4 ~ 'Primary school (Grade 4)',
      grade %in% 5:9 ~ 'Secondary school (Grades 5-9)',
      grade %in% 10:11 ~ 'High school (Grades 10 and 11)'
    ),
    grade2 = factor(
      grade2,
      levels = c(
        'Primary school (Grade 4)',
        'Secondary school (Grades 5-9)',
        'High school (Grades 10 and 11)'
      )
    )
  ) %>%
  ggplot(
    aes(
      x = k0,
      y = k1,
      color = grade2,
      shape = grade2,
      fill = grade2
    )
  ) %>%
  cor_plot
